{
    "text": "Two weeks into Operation Epic Fury, the military campaign to dismantle Iran's ballistic and nuclear capabilities has triggered a global crisis. While the initial air assault targeted air defenses and naval assets, the Iranian regime remains in power and is lashing out. The conflict has rapidly escalated across the Middle East with Iranian missiles striking Israel and American bases. Beyond the immediate combat zones, the humanitarian toll is staggering. The United Nations reports that over 3 million people are now displaced as civilians flee major cities. Economically, the world is reeling as the Strait of Hormuz remains effectively choked off, disrupting 20% of the global oil supply. In response to surging costs, European governments are moving to crack down on price gouging by energy firms. This escalation has left Washington's Gulf allies in a state of profound shock as regional stability evaporates. Despite U.S. efforts to pivot away from the Middle East, this conflict proves the region continues to dominate American foreign policy.",
